definitions.definition: That which is peculiar; a sole or exclusive property; a prerogative; a characteristic.
an ecclesiastical district, parish , chapel or church outside the jurisdiction of the bishop of the diocese in which it is situated.

main_definition: That which is peculiar; a sole or exclusive property; a prerogative; a characteristic.
secondary_definitions: ( UK , canon law ) an ecclesiastical district, parish , chapel or church outside the jurisdiction of the bishop of the diocese in which it is situated.
